--- !u!114 &1040711640
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1040711639}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: c9ffb15eacbbe41428e8c344fbbf0b04, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: Assembly-CSharp::StoryDialogueController
  speakerNameText: {fileID: 131203793}
  dialogueText: {fileID: 1893386491}
  continueIndicator: {fileID: 65937482}
  dialogueLines:
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: 'Alright... here we are. Another long night I was hoping to avoid.

      Office
      building, top floor. One body inside, one gun.

      On the surface, it looks
      simple. Too simple.'
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: 'Man in his late 60s. Former prosecutor. Name: Han Jae-min.

      They
      say he was about to retire. Finally leave all this behind.

      He was working
      on a book. About an old case no one likes to talk about.'
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: "He kept saying, 'This time, I\u2019ll write it the way it really happened.'\r\nFunny
      thing... that line never reached the official reports."
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: "Anyway. Someone decided he should not finish that book.\r\nSo now he\u2019s
      on the floor in there, and we get to clean up the story."
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: "Listen. I\u2019m too old for this, and I was really planning to retire
      quietly.\r\nBut since you\u2019re here... I might as well do one proper lesson
      before I disappear.\r\nYou learn, I finally get to rest. Fair trade, right?"
  - speakerName: Kane
    message: "You\u2019ve got your AR toys. That\u2019s nice.\r\nBut tools don\u2019t
      solve cases. People do.\r\nI\u2019ll show you how to use them so they don\u2019t
      destroy someone\u2019s life by mistake."
  tapAnywhereToAdvance: 1
  minimumAdvanceInterval: 0.15
  nextSceneName: CrimeScene
  loadNextSceneOnComplete: 1
